quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  77,46,"[O disbelievers], eat and enjoy yourselves a little; indeed, you are criminals."
  77,47,"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."
  77,48,"And when it is said to them, "
  79,37,"So as for he who transgressed"
  79,38,"And preferred the life of the world,"
  79,39,"Then indeed, Hellfire will be [his] refuge."
  80,34,"On the Day a man will flee from his brother"
  80,35,"And his mother and his father"
  80,36,"And his wife and his children,"
  83,22,"Indeed, the righteous will be in pleasure"
  83,23,"On adorned couches, observing."
  83,24,"You will recognize in their faces the radiance of pleasure."
  84,19,"[That] you will surely embark upon [i.e., experience] state after state.{1}",1:[i.e., various stages, both in this life and in the Hereafter.]
  84,20,"So what is [the matter] with them [that] they do not believe,"
  84,21,"And when the Qur’ān is recited to them, they do not prostrate [to Allāh]?"
  85,16,"Effecter of what He intends."
  85,17,"Has there reached you the story of the soldiers -"
  85,18,"[Those of] Pharaoh and Thamūd?"
  86,10,"Then he [i.e., man] will have no power or any helper."
  86,11,"By the sky which sends back{1}",1:[Rain, heat, sound waves, etc.]
  86,12,"And [by] the earth which splits,{1}",1:[With plant growth or from geological rifts.]
  87,7,"Except what Allāh should will. Indeed, He knows what is declared and what is hidden."
  87,8,"And We will ease you toward ease.{1}",1:[To the path of Allāh's religion, which is easy and natural, or toward Paradise, by giving opportunities for righteous deeds.]
  87,9,"So remind, if the reminder should benefit;{1}",1:[i.e., wherever it will be heard and understood.]
  88,4,"They will [enter to] burn in an intensely hot Fire."
  88,5,"They will be given drink from a boiling spring."
  88,6,"For them there will be no food except from a poisonous, thorny plant"
  89,1,"By the dawn"
  89,2,"And [by] ten nights{1}",1:[Usually interpreted as the first ten nights of the month of Dhul-Ḥijjah.]
  89,3,"And [by] the even [number] and the odd"